OL,6,F"However, the compliance officer
OL,7,Fconsiders the frequent use of Ipsa-
OL,8,Ffunded office equipment such as the
OL,9,F'Riso' printer went beyond the bounds
OL,10,Fof this agreement, even if some of the
OL,11,Fcosts of use were covered by the local
OL,12,FConservative Association.
OL,14,F"In addition, it is reasonable to
OL,15,Fassume the constituency office was
OL,16,Fused for storage and preparation of
OL,17,Fparty-political material at various
OL,18,Ftimes which are not accurately
OL,19,Freflected in the log of use maintained
OL,20,Fby the MP's office."
